  88:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****               ##### Initialization and de-initialization functions #####
  89:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****  ===============================================================================
  90:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****     [..]  This section provides functions allowing to:
  91:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****       (+) Initializes the NVIC allocation and initial clock configuration.
  92:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****           It initializes the systick also when timeout is needed
  93:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****           and the backup domain when enabled.
  94:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****       (+) De-Initializes common part of the HAL.
  95:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****       (+) Configure The time base source to have 1ms time base with a dedicated
  96:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****           Tick interrupt priority.
  97:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****         (++) SysTick timer is used by default as source of time base, but user
  98:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              can eventually implement his proper time base source (a general purpose
  99:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              timer for example or other time source), keeping in mind that Time base
 100:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              duration should be kept 1ms since PPP_TIMEOUT_VALUEs are defined and
 101:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              handled in milliseconds basis.
 102:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****         (++) Time base configuration function (HAL_InitTick ()) is called automatically
 103:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              at the beginning of the program after reset by HAL_Init() or at any time
 104:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              when clock is configured, by HAL_RCC_ClockConfig().
 105:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****         (++) Source of time base is configured  to generate interrupts at regular
 106:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              time intervals. Care must be taken if HAL_Delay() is called from a
 107:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              peripheral ISR process, the Tick interrupt line must have higher priority
 108:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****             (numerically lower) than the peripheral interrupt. Otherwise the caller
 109:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****             ISR process will be blocked.
 110:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****        (++) functions affecting time base configurations are declared as __weak
 111:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****              to make  override possible  in case of other  implementations in user file.
 112:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c **** @endverbatim
 113:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   * @{
 114:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   */
 115:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c **** 
 116:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c **** /**
 117:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   * @brief  Configure the time base source, NVIC and any required global low
 118:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *         level hardware by calling the HAL_MspInit() callback function to be optionally defined
 119:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *         in user file stm32n6xx_hal_msp.c.
 120:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *
 121:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   * @note   HAL_Init() function is called at the beginning of program after reset and before
 122:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *         the clock configuration.
 123:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *
 124:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   * @note   In the default implementation the System Timer (Systick) is used as source of time base
 125:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *         The Systick configuration is based on HSI clock, as HSI is the clock
 126:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *         used after a system Reset and the NVIC configuration is set to Priority group 4.
 127:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *         Once done, time base tick starts incrementing: the tick variable counter is incremented
 128:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *         each 1ms in the SysTick_Handler() interrupt handler.
 129:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   *
 130:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   * @retval HAL status
 131:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal.c ****   */
